<p><strong>History</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Naming: after dwarf planet Ceres, itself named after Roman deity of agriculture Ceres</li>
<li>Discovery: Martin Heinrich Klaproth, Jöns Jakob Berzelius &amp; Wilhelm Hisinger (1803)</li>
<li>First isolation: Carl Gustaf Mosander (1838)</li>
</ul>
